    $( B&eacute;zout's identity:  For any integers ` A ` and ` B ` , there are
       integers ` x , y ` such that ` ( A gcd B ) = A x. x + B x. y ` .
       (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 22-Feb-2014.) $)
    bezout $p |- ( ( A e. ZZ /\ B e. ZZ ) ->
           E. x e. ZZ E. y e. ZZ ( A gcd B ) = ( ( A x. x ) + ( B x. y ) ) ) $=
      ( vz vu vv vt cz wcel cc0 wceq co cv cmul caddc wrex cn opreq2 eqeq2d clt
      wa cgcd wn crab cr ccnv csup weq 2rexbidv opreq1d rexbidv opreq2d cbvrexv
      eqeq1 syl6bb cbvrabv simpll simplr eqid simpr bezoutlem4 elrab simprbi ex
      syl 0z 0cn mul01i opreq12i gcd0val 3eqtr4ri rcla42ev mp3an opreq12 opreq1
      00id opreqan12d eqeq12d mpbiri pm2.61d2 ) CIJZDIJZUBZCKLZDKLZUBZCDUCMZCAN
      ZOMZDBNZOMZPMZLZBIQAIQZWDWGUDZWOWDWPUBZWHENZWMLZBIQAIQZERUEZJZWOWQFGHCDXA
